  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to determine whether probiotic bacterium Bifidobacterium longum
      (B. longum) can improve mood and bowel symptoms in patients with Irritable bowel syndrome
      (IBS). The patients will be treated with probiotic or placebo for 6 weeks. Their mood,
      memory, general well-being and bowel symptoms will be assessed before, at the end of the
      treatment and 4 weeks later. Brain activation pattern, changes in gut bacteria, metabolic
      profile and inflammatory markers will be also measured.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
